{"title": "Scalp Hunters", "description": "\"Unroll the world\u2019s map, and look upon the great northern continent of America. Away to the wild west, away toward the setting sun, away beyond many a far meridian, let your eyes wander. Rest them where golden rivers rise among peaks that carry the eternal snow. Rest them there.\n<br><br>\nYou are looking upon a land whose features are un-furrowed by human hands, still bearing the marks of the Almighty mould, as upon the morning of creation; a region whose every object wears the impress of God\u2019s image. His ambient spirit lives in the silent grandeur of its mountains, and speaks in the roar of its mighty rivers: a region redolent of romance, rich in the reality of adventure.\n<br><br>\nFollow me, with the eye of your mind, through scenes of wild beauty, of savage sublimity.\"\n<br><br>\nSo begins this early book by Mayne Reid, a book of romance, of adventure, and of the wide open spaces of the Wild West.  (Adapted from the first chapter)", "duration": 43747, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2747", "name": "Thomas Mayne Reid"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/scalp_hunters_1506_librivox/scalp_hunters_1506.jpg", "copyright_year": "1860", "genres": ["Action & Adventure"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ann Boulais"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Wild West", "readers": [7675], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/scalp_hunters_1506_librivox/scalphunters_01_reid_64kb.mp3", "duration": 829}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Prairie Merchant", "readers": [7879], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/scalp_hunters_1506_librivox/scalphunters_02_reid_64kb.mp3", "duration": 582}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Prairie Fever", "readers": [7675], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/scalp_hunters_1506_librivox/sc